Kualiti Hidup Peserta Program Ladang Kontrak di Bawah Pertubuhan Peladang 
Kawasan 
The Quality of Life among Contract Farming Programme Participants under Local Farmers Association 
Rosniza Aznie Che Rose*& Tee Meng Yong 
Fakulti Sains Sosial dan Kemanusiaan,  
Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia, 43600 Bangi, Selangor 
*
emel: aznie@ukm.edu.my 
 
Received: 7 August 2017; Accepted: 6 October 2017; Published: 31 December 2017 
 
Abstrak 
Kajian ini dilakukan untuk mengenal pasti sumbangan Pertubuhan Peladang Kawasan (PPK) dan tahap penyertaan 
peserta PPK dalam program ladang kontrak di Selangor Darul Ehsan. Kerangka kajian berdasarkan kepada dua teori 
utama iaitu gabungan tipologi Pretty dan model Arnstein yang digunakan untuk mengkaji tahap penglibatan peserta 
program ladang kontrak dan sumbangan-sumbangan PPK dalam ladang kontrak. Persampelan mudah dipilih dalam 
pelaksanaan kajian ini yang melibatkan seramai 108 daripada 145 jumlah keseluruhan peserta program ladang kontrak 
di bawah PPK. Walau bagaimanapun, daripada 108 borang soal selidik yang diedarkan hanya 98 jawapan responden 
yang diterima. Hasil kajian menunjukkan bahawa PPK bawah program ladang kontrak ternyata dapat meningkatkan 
kualiti hidup peserta dari aspek pendapatan dan pengagihan, pendidikan, kesihatan dan keluarga dengan sumbangan-
sumbangan PPK yang dikenal pasti berada dalam lingkungan 82.7 hingga 91.8 peratus. Sementara itu, tahap 
penyertaan peserta PPK di bawah program ladang kontrak boleh dikatakan pada tahap penglibatan akar umbi dan agak 
memberangsangkan. Penglibatan yang berada pada tahap tinggi adalah penglibatan berfungsi, penglibatan interaktif 
dan penglibatan pergerakan sendiri. Ini sejajar dengan peringkat kuasa komuniti (citizen power) dalam model Arnstein 
di mana peserta mempunyai kuasa penuh ke atas penglibatan. Lanjutan daripada itu, dengan memahami sumbangan 
PPK dan tahap penyertaan peserta PPK di kawasan kajian, Kementerian Pertanian dan Industri Asas Tani serta 
jabatan/agensi di bawahnya dapat melakukan penambahbaikan dalam memastikan pelaksanaan program ladang 
kontrak ini benar-benar mencapai sasaran dan golongan sasaran. 
Kata kunci kualiti hidup, Pertubuhan Peladang Kawasan, peserta, program ladang kontrak, petani  
Abstract 
This study was conducted to identify the contribution of the Local Farmers Association (PPK) and the level of 
participation of PPK participants in the contract farming program in Selangor Darul Ehsan. The framework of the 
study is based on two main theories namely the combination of Pretty typology and the Arnstein model used to examine 
the level of engagement of contract farming program participants and its contributions in contract farming. 
Convenience sampling is selected in the implementation of this study involving 108 out of 145 total program 
participants contract farm under Local Farmers Association. However, out of 108 questionnaires distributed only 98 
responses were received. The findings show that PPK under the contract farming program was able to improve the 
quality of life of participants in terms of income and distribution, education, health and family with the contribution 
of Local Farmers Association identified within the range of 82.7 to 91.8 percent. Meanwhile, the level of PPK 
participant’s participation under the contract farming program can be said at the grassroots level of engagement and is 
quite encouraging. High-level engagements are functional participation, interactive participation and self-mobilisation. 
These are in line with the Citizen Power in Arnstein model where participants have full authority over engagement. 
Furthermore, by understanding the contribution of PPK and the level of participation of PPK participants in the study 
area, the Ministry of Agriculture and Agro-based Industry, as well as the departments/agencies under it may make 
improvements in ensuring the implementation of this Contract Farming Program really achieves targets and target 
groups. 
Keywords quality of life, local farmers association, participants, contract farming programme, farmer  
